Name: moderation
Description: Text moderation scans text for offensive, sexually explicit or suggestive content, it checks also if there is any content of self-harm, violence, racist or hate speech.

Name: summarize
Description: Summarization is the act of condensing a piece of written text into a summarized and more concise version, without losing the crucial details that convey the essence of the original text.

Name: automatic_translation
Description: Automatic translation or machine translation (MT) is the process of automatically translating a text from one language to another using computer-based techniques. The aim of it is to enable people to communicate and access information in different languages, without the need for human intervention.

Name: ocr
Description: Optical Character Recognition or Reader (OCR) is the electronic or mechanical conversion of images of typed, handwritten or printed text into machine-encoded text. The image can be a scanned document or a photo of a license plate, a road sign or anything else that contains text (type of files allowed: jpg, jpeg, png, tiff) .

Name: receipt_parser
Description: Receipt Parser makes it possible to extract structured information like products purchased, quantity, price, date, VAT amount in a structured format from unstructured receipts (images or scanned documents).

Name: generation
Description: Text generation is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP). It leverages knowledge in computational linguistics and artificial intelligence to automatically generate natural language texts, which can satisfy certain communicative requirements. It is based on large language models.

Name: syntax_analysis
Description: Syntax analysis is a the process that involves identifying and highlighting the structural elements of a text. By breaking down a piece of writing into its constituent parts, including words, phrases, and sentences, syntax analysis enables us to better understand the author's intended meaning and message. (character limit: <1000)

Name: object_detection
Description: Object Detection is a computer vision technique that allows users to identify and locate (with bounding boxes) objects in an image. The detected objects can be animals, people, electronics, vehicles etc. (type of file allowed: jpg, jpeg, png, tiff)

Name: invoice_parser
Description: The OCR Invoice API enables customers to take invoices in a variety of formats and returns the data in contains (items, prices, addresses, vendor name, etc.) in a structured format to automate the invoice processing. (type of files allowed: pdf, jpg, jpeg, png)

Name: explicit_content
Description: Explicit Content Detection detects adult only content in images, that is generally inappropriate for people under the age of 18 and includes nudity, sexual activity, pornography, violence, gore content, etc. (type of files allowed: jpg, jpeg, png, tiff)

Name: speech_to_text_async
Description: Speech Recognition (or speech to text) can recognize and transcribe spoken words (voice),  that will be converted to text with or without diarization. It is also possible to filter profanity. The type of files allowed: mp3, wav, m4a. If convert_to_wav option is set to true, then you can transcribe any type of audio or video files.

Name: spell_check
Description: Spell Check analyzes the  inputted text by and compares it to a dictionary of correctly spelled words to identify and highlight any spelling errors or grammatical mistakes.

Name: face_detection
Description: Face Detection is a computer technology being used in a variety of applications that identifies human faces in digital images with different attributes like landmark, sentiment and what they are wearing (type of file allowed: jpg, jpeg, png, tiff)

Name: ocr_tables_async
Description: OCR Table (Optical Character Recognition for tabular documents)  allows users to analyze documents containing tables and return structured representation of the detected tables in the form of a Json object that can be converted to a CSV.

Name: sentiment_analysis
Description: Sentiment Analysis inspects the given text and identifies the prevailing emotional opinion within the text, especially to determine a writer's attitude as positive, negative, or neutral.  Also called "opinion mining", it identifies and detect subjective information from the input text.

Name: topic_extraction
Description: Topic analysis is a Natural Language Processing (NLP) technique that allows us to automatically extract meaning from text by identifying recurrent themes or topics.

Name: named_entity_recognition
Description: Named Entity Recognition (also called entity identification or extraction) is an information extraction technique that automatically identifies named entities in a text and classifies them into predefined categories such as dates, persons names, company names, dates, products etc.

Name: search
Description: Searching for images using an image as a query is also refereed to as content based image retrieval (CBIR). It allows a user to look for and extract images in an existing database that are similar to a query image.

Name: text_detection_async
Description: Video Text Detection is a video analysis feature that uses optical character recognition (OCR) technology to extract text present in a video, making it searchable and easily accessible.

Name: custom_document_parsing_async
Description: Custom Document Parser allows extraction of specific information from text-based documents using a query. Simply provide the text you want to search and the system will use optical character recognition (OCR) technology to scan the document and extract the information you need by automatically finding the specific data within large amounts of text, making it ideal for tasks such as data entry and analysis. It can also reply to yes/no questions to help classify a document

Name: identity_parser
Description: ID Document parsing technology allows users to automatically extract information from an ID Document such as passport, ID card, driving license and more. This API is ideal for developers looking to create applications that require identity verification or access control. It extracts information like name, date of birth, nationality, age and more.

Name: keyword_extraction
Description: Keyword extraction (also known as keyword detection or keyword analysis) is a text analysis technique that consists of automatically extracting the most important words and expressions that better represent the input text.

Name: resume_parser
Description: Resume Parser enables users to extract various information from resumes that could be in a variety of formats and returns structured data (name, job list, education, skills) to automate their processing. (type of files allowed: pdf, jpg, jpeg, png)

Name: face_detection_async
Description: Face Detection: A feature that identifies and locates human faces within a video, allowing for focused analysis on specific individuals or for applications such as facial recognition and landmarks analysis.

Name: logo_detection_async
Description: This AI-powered video analysis tool is specifically designed to detect logos and trademarks within videos, making it an indispensable asset for companies seeking to protect their brand identity and monitor their online presence. It can also be used for targeted advertising campaigns, allowing businesses to easily identify potential opportunities for promotion.

Name: explicit_content_detection_async
Description: This features allows the user to detect if a video contains explicit content like adult material or any vulgar, (nudity, sexual activity, pornography)  gore or violent content so that developers can restrict the display of these videos in their software.

Name: label_detection_async
Description: Automatically detects and categorizes objects, people, and other items present in a video into predefined categories such as animals, buildings, and landmarks.

Name: face_recognition
Description: Recognizing a face in an image is a more advanced feature than just detecting the face in the image. It allows the user to search for the detected face in an image in an existing database of images and extract the faces that are most similar to the face  displayed in the query image.

Name: language_detection
Description: Language detection, also known as language identification, refers to the process of determining the natural language in which a given piece of content is written. This involves the use of algorithms to analyze the textual data and identify the specific linguistic features that are unique to each language.

Name: landmark_detection
Description: Landmark Detection is the task of identifying and recognizing popular natural and human-made structures such as famous buildings, monuments.  It helps identify where an an image was taken. Landmark Detection is widely used in a variety of applications, including travel and tourism, social media, and digital mapping services, to provide users with more personalized and engaging experiences.

Name: anonymization
Description: The personally identifiable information (PII) detection feature can identify, categorize, and redact sensitive information in unstructured text. For example: phone numbers, email addresses, and forms of identification. The method for utilizing PII in conversations is different than other use cases, and articles for this use have been separated. Removing these personally identifiable information helps with the Anonymization of a text and privacy protection.

Name: logo_detection
Description: Logo Detection is a powerful technology that enables the automatic identification and recognition of popular logos within an image. It provides accurate and efficient detection of known (and less known) brand logos. It's a valuable tool for a variety of industries, including advertising, retail, and e-commerce.

Name: custom_classification
Description: Custom Text Classification allows users to categorize their text by automatically setting a label for them from a predefined set of categories that the users indicate. It is based on few shot examples of texts and their wanted classes that it generalizes from to handle a different set of texts

Name: object_tracking_async
Description: Object Tracking identifies, detect and track known objects (vehicles, electronics, everyday objects, plants or animals) within a video. It can help for example describe the content of the video and what's happening there.

Name: anonymization
Description: Image Anonymization API, also known as image de-identification or image de-personalization, refers to the process of automatically removing personal or sensitive information from images. The main objective is to protect the privacy and security of individuals who may be depicted in images shared online or used for research purposes.

Name: person_tracking_async
Description: This cutting-edge video analysis technology is capable of tracking and following individual people as they move within a video, enabling focused analysis on specific individuals. This tool is especially useful for security and surveillance applications, as well as for marketing research and audience profiling. It provides insights into the behaviors and movements of people within a video.

Name: code_generation
Description: Code Generation uses models that has been trained on both natural language and billions of lines of code in different programming languages. These models can be used for a variety of tasks including adding comments into code, completing your next line or a function in a given context,  finding a useful library or API for an application, adding comments or also rewriting code for efficiency. It can also be fine tuned for other tasks like command generation

Name: generation
Description: Image Generation is an advanced feature that generates compelling images based on a given text prompt. It can easily produce high-quality and original images in a matter of seconds, without the need for specialized design skills or software

Name: custom_named_entity_recognition
Description: Custom Named Entity Recognition (NER) or extraction is an information extraction technique that automatically identifies named entities in a text and classifies them into a specific set of predefined categories that can be specified by users to fit their exact needs. Custom NER enables users customize AI models to extract domain-specific entities from unstructured text. The quality of the examples the models base their prediction on greatly impacts the performance

Name: document_translation
Description: Document Translation API translates whole documents in supported languages and various file formats (like pdf or doc) by keeping their structure intact.

Name: text_to_speech
Description: Text-to-speech (TTS) system is a technology that enables the generation of high-quality audio from a written text while offering the flexibility to choose the desired voice, including male or female voices, and more. It utilizes advanced algorithms and neural networks to synthesize speech that closely resembles human speech, making it an ideal solution for a wide range of applications, including virtual assistants, audiobooks, and accessibility tools for people with visual impairments or reading difficulties. With TTS technology, it is possible to convert text into spoken words with remarkable accuracy and naturalness, providing an immersive and engaging listening experience.

Name: search
Description: Text Search allows you to do a semantic search over a set of textual documents. This means that you can provide a query, such as a natural language question or a statement, and the provided documents will be scored and ranked based on how semantically related they are to the input query.

Name: question_answer
Description: Given a question, a set of documents, and some examples, the Question Answering generates an answer to the question based on the information present in the given set of textual documents. This is useful for question-answering applications on sources of truth, like company documentation or a knowledge base.
